  "prompt": "What is luvox good for?",
  "response": "Luvox is the brand name for fluvoxamine, which is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) commonly prescribed to treat several mental health conditions. **Luvox is primarily used for:**\n\n1. **Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD):** It helps reduce the symptoms of OCD, such as obsessive thoughts and compulsive behaviors.\n2. **Depression:** Luvox may be prescribed to alleviate depressive symptoms in some individuals.\n3. **Anxiety Disorders:** It can be used to manage various anxiety-related conditions, including social anxiety disorder and panic disorder.\n4. **Other Uses:** In some cases, Luvox is prescribed off-label for conditions like post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) or certain eating disorders.\n\n**Important Note:** While Luvox can be effective for these conditions, it may not be suitable for everyone and can have side effects. It's essential to use this medication under the supervision and guidance of a qualified healthcare professional.\n\nIf you have questions or concerns about Luvox or its suitability for your situation, please consult with your doctor or a mental health specialist.",
